cyrus-sasl (1.5.27-2.1) unstable; urgency=high

  * NMU
  * Apply patch against SASL re-entrancy design problems
    (avoids chain-crashing postfix-tls using SASL LDAP auth)
    Patch by Rein Tollevik <rein@basefarm.no>
    Release Manager: without this patch, all applications that
    both link to OpenLDAP and use SASL (maybe through PAM) will
    segfault.  The patch is quite simple and should not
    break anything (closes: #139568)

